The functional requirements describe what the Smart Queue Management System for Banks must do to support efficient queue handling and service management.

FR-01: Customer Token Generation
Description:
The system shall allow bank customers to generate a virtual token for service.
Acceptance Criteria:
•	Customer can successfully generate a token
•	A unique token number is assigned
•	Token is added to the active queue
FR-02: Display Queue Status
Description:
The system shall display the current queue status to customers and staff.
Acceptance Criteria:
•	Queue list is visible on display screens
•	Token order is accurate and updated in real time
FR-03: Call Next Token
Description:
The system shall allow bank tellers to call the next token in the queue.
Acceptance Criteria:
•	Only the next valid token is called
•	Token status changes to “In Service”
FR-04: Service Counter Management
Description:
The system shall support multiple service counters within a bank branch.
Acceptance Criteria:
•	Counters can be added or removed by admin
•	Each called token is linked to a counter
FR-05: Notification to Customers
Description:
The system shall notify customers when their turn is approaching.
Acceptance Criteria:
•	Notification is triggered before the turn
•	Notification content is clear and accurate
FR-06: User Authentication
Description:
The system shall provide secure login access for tellers and administrators.
Acceptance Criteria:
•	Only authorized users can log in
•	Invalid login attempts are rejected
FR-07: Admin Dashboard Access
Description:
The system shall provide an admin dashboard for monitoring queue activities.
Acceptance Criteria:
•	Admin can view queue statistics
•	Admin can manage counters and users
FR-08: Report Generation
Description:
The system shall generate basic operational reports.
Acceptance Criteria:
•	Reports include number of customers served
•	Reports can be viewed or downloaded
